summary: I think dan and phil would be more appreciated now in 2019 if they tried to be more real instead on trying “to fit into” these...
question: I think dan and phil would be more appreciated now in 2019 if they tried to be more real instead on trying “to fit into” these personas they created long ago.
answer: I could not agree more. They are played out and easy to see through at this point. People like Dan and Phil for their personalities, because the fact that they are interesting, funny, creative, kind human beings shows through, even when their branding is annoying. If they just went with that and dropped the over-manufacrured personas that we’re popular on YouTube a few years back, I think they would at least attract some of the people who stopped watching them because they grew out of that, who would give their new content a chance. Take Daniel and Depression for instance, people loved that because it was Dan being real. It got a lot of well-deserved attention and praise. They don’t have to share their personal lives to be more real in my opinion either. There is a happy medium.
